# VisuDEV agent workflow

- Run `npm run checks` before push/deploy. Prefer `npm run push` or `git push` (pre-push hook + AI review).
- Never bypass the Supabase shim — use `bash scripts/supabase-checked.sh` or `npm run supabase:checked`, not raw `npx supabase`.
- AI review: score ≥ 95% and verdict ACCEPT required. On REJECT: read `.shimwrapper/review-failed.json` and latest `.shimwrapper/reviews/*.md`, fix **all** deductions with a broad pass per affected file, then re-run checks.
- Do not push to `main`/`master` unless explicitly instructed. Feature work on `issue/*` branches.
- Do not delete lockfiles to fix builds — regenerate with a compatible tool version.
- Secrets: never commit `.env`, `.env.local`, or anon keys. Cloud anon key via `.env.cloud.example` → `.env.local`.
- Components live in `src/components/` (shared UI only). Domain code in `src/modules/<domain>/`.

See `AGENTS.md` for full rules.
